    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that, but it feels like youre leaning pretty hard on the \"unintended consequences\" bit. wouldn't it be more accurate to say it was a failure because it actually destabilized an entire region and helped spread chaos across the sahel? or is there a legitimate strategic argument that it actually served national interests in the long run?",
